## Content Authoring

Content is written in markdown with YAML frontmatter:

```markdown
---
type: ProfileHero
variant: researcher
photoPosition: left
---

# Dr. Sarah Chen

## Associate Professor of Computer Science

Bio text here...

![Photo](photo.jpg)

[Email](mailto:sarah@university.edu)
[Google Scholar](https://scholar.google.com)
```

### Markdown Conventions

- **H1 (#)** — Main title (person name, page title)
- **H2 (##)** — Subtitle (position, tagline)
- **H3 (###)** — Item titles (paper titles, member names)
- **H4 (####)** — Group headers (years, roles, publication types)

