## Development

### Running Individual Packages

```bash
# Foundation dev server (component development)
pnpm --filter foundation dev

# Site dev server (content development)
pnpm --filter site dev
```

### Creating New Components

1. Create folder: `foundation/src/components/MyComponent/`
2. Add `index.jsx` with the React component
3. Add `meta.js` with metadata and parameters (see [meta.js guide](https://github.com/uniweb/cli/blob/main/docs/meta/README.md))
4. Rebuild: `cd foundation && pnpm build`

Components are auto-discovered from `meta.js` — no manual registration needed.

### Using @uniweb/scholar

The foundation includes `@uniweb/scholar` for academic content:

```jsx
// Citation formatting
import { formatReference, CiteButton, DoiLink } from '@uniweb/scholar'

// Math rendering (KaTeX, lazy-loaded)
import { Math, Equation, EquationProvider } from '@uniweb/scholar/math'

// Bibliography management
import { CitationProvider, Citation, Bibliography } from '@uniweb/scholar/citations'
```

See `AGENTS.md` for detailed component development guidelines.

